description:
In this episode, we learn about the life of Moses, who did not have the easiest start in life. Moses was born during tumultuous times, being raised in the palace of Pharaoh. However, he had to flee to the wilderness where he was prepared for the difficult task ahead. Finally, after Children of Israel had been in Egypt for 400 years, God decided that his people needed to leave, and the man destined to lead them was Moses.
